Task: Build the Project section of the portfolio, following the same architectural patterns, conventions, and feature set used in the Skills section (core files provided). The Project store file is also provided as a starting point.

Requirements:

1. Card UI Styles & Configurations
   - Project cards must support multiple distinct style variants and configuration options, ensuring the portfolio showcases a mix of design flavors rather than uniform cards.

2. Field-Level Toggle
   - Every individual piece of information within an Project entry must be independently toggleable (show/hide).

3. Layout Types
   - Provide layout types specifically designed for displaying Project in a professional standard.
   - These layouts must be visually and structurally distinct from the layouts used in the Skills section.

4. Public Filters
   - Implement filter controls for public users using the following ProjectFilters interface exactly:
     export interface PublicProjectFilters {
     issuing_organization?: string;
     ids?: string[];
     merge_filters?: boolean;
     }

5. Card Override Support
   - Project must continue to support card-level overrides, following the same override pattern used in the Skills section.

6. Animations, Background & CTA
   - Implement Animations, Background, and CTA for Project exactly as they were done in the Skills section — same behavior, same integration points.

7. File Naming Conventions
   - Follow the same file naming conventions established in the Skills section to ensure consistency and ease of debugging.

8. Type Definitions
   - Project must have its own dedicated type file.
   - Types may be inherited/reused from other type files where applicable, but the Project-specific type file must still exist and own its domain types.

Deliverable: Assemble all created files into a .zip file and present it.

